WorkloadCertificateFeature.description: Represents the Managed Workload Certificate feature. This is a singleton resource of a project that contains the mode of the feature, trust-domain-level configurations, and etc. go/workloadcert-enablement-api.

name.description: Output only. Name of the resource. Format: `projects/*/locations/global/workloadCertificateFeature`.

defaultSpec.description: Optional. Workload certificate feature spec for the default project level trust domain (i.e. `.svc.id.goog`). If left unset, the feature is disabled.

defaultStatus.description: Output only. The current WorkloadCertificate feature status of the default project level trust domain.

WorkloadCertificateFeatureSpec.description: Spec for the workload certificate feature.

mode.description: The mode for the workload certificate feature.
enumDescriptions: Workload certificate feature is enabled, and the entire certificate provisioning process is managed by Google, including the CA.

WorkloadCertificateFeatureStatus.description: Status of Workload Certificate feature at trust domain level.

managedCaPools.description: A map from a region to the status of managed CA pools in that region.

state.description: Describes whether the Workload Certificate feature meets its spec.
enumDescriptions: The feature status does not fully meet its spec at the moment but is trying to meet its spec.
The feature status does not fully meet its spec at the moment but is trying to meet its spec.
The feature status currently meets its spec.
The feature status does not fully meet its spec at the moment due to an internal error. Contact support.

CaPoolsStatus.description: Status of CA pools in a region.

caPools.description: The CA pool string has a relative resource path following the form "projects/{project_number}/locations/{location}/caPools/{ca_pool}".

workloadNamespace.description: workload_namespace specifies the namespace (which must exist in the same project) the workloads are registered to. It's skipped for k8s workloads, but required for non-k8s workloads. optional.

workloadSelector.description: Criteria used to select the specific group of workloads in the registry on which this patch configuration should be applied. required.

status.description: Output only. The status of the workloadregistration resource.

WorkloadSelector.description: WorkloadSelector specifies the criteria used to determine if a rule can be applied to a group of workload. The matching criteria is based on workload types.

gcpWorkloadSelector.description: Selects a group of GCP workloads.

K8SWorkloadSelector.description: For kubernetes workloads, fleet_member_id is used as workload selector.

fleetMemberId.description: Fleet membership ID (only the name part, not the full URI). The “project” and “location” of the membership is the same as the WorkloadRegistration. required.

GCPWorkloadSelector.description: GCPWorkloadSelector selects a group of GCP workloads, like GCE or load balancer.

type.description: Type pecifies the workload type. It is either indicated by the identity dataplane P4SA, or in the resource identity case, the resource service (“google.resource.service” claim). required.
enumDescriptions: Default value. This value is unused and this field is invalid.

project.description: Project specifies the workloads’ project in the format of "". required.

attribute.description: GCPAttributeSelector selects a group of workloads that match the attribute. optional.

GCPAttributeSelector.description: GCPAttributeSelector is an “oneof” field, which can be a Google service account, a resource identity, etc. If not specified, all workloads of the given type in the project are selected.

serviceAccount.description: Selects workloads with the GCP service account. It matches the “email” claim.

RegistrationStatus.description: RegistrationStatus describes the certificate provisioning status of a workload registration resource.

state.description: state represents the current state of registration.
enumDescriptions: REGISTRATION_STATE_READY indicates that the registration is ready.
REGISTRATION_STATE_IN_PROGRESS indicates that the registration is in progress.
REGISTRATION_STATE_INTERNAL_ERROR indicates that the registration fails because of some internal errors.

error.description: error describes the details when a certificate provisioning process fails.
